column5: Hi all,  After a long, dreary, wet and windy day nursing the mother of all trapped nerves in my neck i had to get out....Jack had been bugging to leave the house all day too. We headed to a sheltered lake i know for an hour shore fishing and some fresh, albeit cold and wet, air.  Nice way to end the day. Dont know what was with my camera settings tonight...but the pictures sucked...you get the idea though.     <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/kQDM3-AjBjc" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
I bet Jack was like hpfff if we had a net Dad don't you think I'd be playing with it??  I always enjoy your reports ,thanks
nice little snot rocket there Simon - Jack will keep you focused on what really matters
Between jack and Roloff, you sure know cute! Looks like a good de-stressing evening.
Thanks MoS....yeah....i should have brought his 'moth catching' net with us!   Yup, perspectives changed drastically and for the better 3 years ago!    Cute is definitely a good stress remedy!
I'm pretty sure I recognize that spot.....from past reports.  One day I'll get up there and at least know my way around a bit!  Great way to live up there....thanks for sharing it with us
